    <item>
      <title>Beach House &amp; Stranger Kings, much dream pop goodness.</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/blog/beach-house-stranger-kings-much-dream-pop-goodness/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2015 19:56:01 +0000</pubDate>
       <guid isPermaLink="false">http://schelp.co.uk/?p=2745</guid> 
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Untitled-1.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Untitled-1&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Untitled-1-300x150.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
I am a sucker for some &lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dream_pop&#34;&gt;dream pop&lt;/a&gt;, and two new music releases of a dream pop type persuasion are soon to be in my possession, (well one on order and one being shipped from the USA). The first is the new album by &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.beachhousebaltimore.com&#34;&gt;Beach House&lt;/a&gt; called &amp;ldquo;Depression Cherry&amp;rdquo;. I have this ordered without hearing anything from it yet, so it better be good&amp;hellip; I am confident it will be, I loved the album &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.metacritic.com/music/bloom&#34;&gt;Bloom&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rdquo; from 2012. It is a remarkably good album, so good it is one of the 38 albums I choose to carry with me on an MP3 device at all times. &lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/PBjxOeVLY3g?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
 The question is whether to buy tickets for Beach House&amp;rsquo;s October 26th Glasgow concert or not. I suspect I will, but I am not sure how rock and roll it will be. (Below is a film Beach House made with performances of 4 songs from Bloom.)&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/lgD8vWIB8hs?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
 The second album I have bought is by a Californian dream pop practitioners called &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.facebook.com/strangerkings?fref=ts&#34;&gt;Stranger Kings&lt;/a&gt;. You can listen to the album on band camp below.  They have gorgeous 80&amp;rsquo;s peter hook influenced base work, dreamy guitars, and a beautiful voice on top, whats not to like right? &lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;
      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/_mCT68qeQJY?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
 mucho musical goodness.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
